 <body>
  <h1>
   current_hour
  </h1>
  This
  <b>
   read only
  </b>
  variable will return the hour that corresponds to the current moment based on the default time zone for the system (ie: local time). You can change the base time zone to use with the function
  <a href="date_set_timezone.htm">
   <span>
    date_set_timezone()
   </span>
  </a>
  .
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">current_hour;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_text(32, 32, "The time is " + string(current_hour) + ":" + string(current_minute) + "." + string(current_second));
</code></pre>
  The above code would draw the current international time on the screen.
 </body>
</html>